Maybe I'll post the next one on Thirstday instead</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/EDKSX3m</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Icouri]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Ladies we need to talk</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/0HkEwOt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BF4YhRx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/32HPILz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Q1WL0ne.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/etfRAbh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WJAWpni.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>14: bled through a pad I had changed 30 minutes prior and my mom thought I was living and told me to do better. 

16: threw up after cooking class in high-school because my period pain was so bad. 

16 - 19: thankfully after this incident my mom finally took me seriously and started to really push my doctor for help. 

I tried 13 different birth controls and they put me on depo because it stopped my periods. It was a short term solution as it's not good to take this forever. 

19: finaly diagnosed with endometriosis. Has surgery. Stopped having pain for 3 months. 

23: finally got checked again for endro after being told for years that they got it all in the first surgery. Had second surgery. 

27: still suffering from pain was referred to gyno and told birth control was my only option. Tried another wackload of pills, was also diagnosed with PCOS and told to lose weight and exercise. 

31: hospitalized from pain every month for 1 year and given iron supplements for anemia. Has sever bloodless over christmas this year and almost need a transfusion. 

32 - 38: have taken at least 1 day off per month around my period because of pain. Coworkers and bosses know why which is humiliating. I get pale skin, fever, pain, vomiting etc. It is hell. 

39: get new doctor. New doctor asks why I haven't tried Dienogest. What's that? Fucking pills for endometriosis. 

Try it. 

Holy effing balls man. No pain. NO PAIN for the first time since I got my period at 13 years old. 

If you are a woman and my story sounds similar I created this post in hopes that my story helps you and you can go ask your doctor for this. 

I don't know what it would cost in the US but here in canada I don't have extended medical and its only costing me $27 a month and it has changed my life. Like literally changed it. Please for the love of God ladies advocate for yourself and get these pills if you have endro  or PCOS and take you life back. 

If you have questions I probably can't help with lots of them because I'm not a doctor. So go see a doc!!!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/0HkEwOt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[veesee]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I swear this is my legit 16th favorite.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7nYitmy</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ACqnS03.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Enjoy hypno bottom.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/7nYitmy</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[housev1l]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Elon is a &quot;tech bro&quot; and doesn't now legacy code</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/deBjaHW</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Tzcm5hR.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>here's the link to the BS https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-14406439/doge-social-security-fraud-dead-people-vampires.html</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WGxHyd8.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Someone needs to tell Katelyn Caralle of the daily mail that she's part of the problem</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HE6fOOy.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>How it works... https://www.dailykos.com/stories/2025/2/14/2303889/-Nope-There-are-no-150-year-olds-on-Social-Security-It-s-COBOL</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/deBjaHW</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[codenametrixie]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Crooks in DC</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/nPVZOZr</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oyDbZwW.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/nPVZOZr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SomeRandomPerson2024]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>2n